Biography

Archduchess of Austria as the daughter of Archduke Franz Salvator and Archduchess Marie Valerie. Through her mother she was a granddaughter of Emperor Franz Joseph I of Austria.

She married at Niederwallsee on 19 September 1912 to Georg Graf von Waldburg zu Zeil und Hohenems (1878–1955). The marriage was one of love and not a political marriage. Georg Graf von Waldburg had no money or property, and had been hired as a tutor for her brothers.

She died on 29 January 1930, aged 38, in Syrgenstein, Austria.

Sy Scholfield forwarded news report from "Bote für Tirol," 28 January 1892, p. 1: "Ihre k. und k. Hoheit die durchlauchtigste Frau Erzherzogin Marie Valerie, Gemahlin Sr. k. und k. Hoheit des durchlauchtigsten Herrn Erzherzogs Franz Salvator, ist am 27. ds., um 3/4 6 Uhr früh, in Wien von einer Erzherzogin glücklich entbunden worden." (Her Royal Highness, the most illustrious Archduchess Marie Valerie, consort of His Majesty, His Highness the most illustrious Archduke Francis Salvator, was happily delivered of an Archduchess in Vienna on the 27th, at three-quarters-before-six [5:45am] in the morning).
